        <description>&lt;img src="https://reddavid.me/images/og/scraping.png" alt="Featured image of post Scraping Facebook Pages to Get Number of Likes and Followers" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ever since Facebookâ€™s New Page Experience update, my app that logs several Facebook pagesâ€™ number of likes and followers have been broken.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prior to that, I was using a simple HttpClient to receive a page response content and scrape off content (HTML element) that holds the values for the likes and followers, respectively, using Nodes() from HtmlDocument().&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everything works just fine then the update happened.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;old-way&#34;&gt;Old Way&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before getting into my &lt;em&gt;working&lt;/em&gt; method, let me show you the old code (redacted as much as possible):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt; 5
